        <p class="note" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;Note: &lt;/b&gt;">You can use the toggle button <img src="../../Images/toggle_double_click_toc_entry_btn.png" class="ReduceButtonSize" /> on the right side of the local toolbar in a TOC or browse sequence if you want to reverse the normal double-click behavior. The default behavior (without the toggle button selected) is that double-clicking an item will open the properties dialog, and holding down the CTRL key while double-clicking will open the file linked to the item. If you activate the toggle button, this behavior is reversed; double-clicking an item opens the file linked to it, and holding the CTRL key while double-clicking will open the properties dialog.</p>
